- Use `uv` for managing Python dependencies and running scripts.
- For installing dependencies, use `uv pip install <package_name>`.
- To install dependencies from `pyproject.toml` (or `requirements.txt`), use `uv pip sync pyproject.toml`.
- To run scripts defined in `pyproject.toml`, use `uv run <script_name>`. For example, `uv run start_server`.
- Keep `pyproject.toml` updated with all project dependencies.
- Use `ruff` for linting Python code.
- Use `ruff format` for formatting Python code.
- Adhere to PEP 8 and other standard Python style guides enforced by `ruff`.
- Run `ruff check --fix .` to lint and automatically fix issues.
- Run `ruff format .` to format all Python files in the project.